  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Prevention of violent extremism and support for reconciliation through quality education</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Quality education can play a decisive role in delivering the foundational tools for the reconciliation of fracture communities under the framework of global citizenship, as well as building the resilience required to resist the push and pull factors associated with violent extremism. At the rquest of the Goverment of Iraq, the action will start to scope this role for education, identifying contextually relevant entry-points and approaches through discussion and investigation, leading towards plans for action.</narrative>
  </description>
